HEADWORD: Auroral
<hw>Au*ro"ral</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Belonging to, or
resembling, the aurora (the dawn or the northern lights);
rosy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her cheeks suffused with an <qex>auroral</qex> blush.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>aurorean</ent>⟦br⟧
